                    <span>This was a wonderful book. This book tells an amazing story about life in Africa for an American woman. The writer is truly gifted. She wrote in such a way as to make the story and the people in it truly come alive. This book was incredibly difficult to put down and when I did I could hardly wait to find out what happened next. She has an amazing ability to make the reader feel as though you are sitting right there watching the story unfold. The writer is able to reveal her deepest feelings on the pages of the book and doesn't hold anything back which truly makes this book a gem. This is a magnificent book and a must read for anyone remotely interested about life in Africa. I can assure you, you won't be dissapointed.</span>
                  
